<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870716-0051 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Combustion Engineering Inc.</HL><DD> 07/16/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CSP </IN><TEXT>   Combustion Engineering Inc. said its Lummus Crest Inc. unit received a $330 million contract to design and construct a coal-fired cogeneration plant and a carbon dioxide production facility for Applied Energy Services Inc. Lummus will be the contractor for the Le Flore County, Okla., project, which is expected to be completed in December 1990. The plant and production facility will be owned by closely held Applied Energy, an Arlington, Va., power project developer. Combustion Engineering, Stamford, Conn., supplies technical services and equipment to utilities and processing plants. </TEXT></DOC>